    <bodyTop>
      <Value><![CDATA[<p>Your years at university present a great opportunity to gain invaluable experience, insight and really build your employability. Part-time jobs, seasonal work, placements, internships and voluntary work are all ways that will help you achieve this.</p>
<p><span class="lead"><strong>How We Can Help</strong></span></p>
<p>We can give <a data-id="1562" href="/{localLink:umb://document/2c872903b70448e8a3a87f023665cf2b}" title="Careers Support Whilst a Student">careers advice while you are a student</a> and help you explore what’s available in the way of part time work, internships, volunteering and graduate level employment as you study. Our <a rel="noopener" href="https://studentcentral.qmu.ac.uk/s/careers" target="_blank" title="Student Central (Vacancies)">online vacancy service</a> is set up to allow you to search for work experience, jobs and volunteering opportunities by sector and location. You can search for opportunities from the moment you arrive at QMU and use the service throughout your degree to gain a variety of useful experiences.</p>
<p><span class="NormalTextRun SCXW119872436 BCX0">We make every effort to ensure the information we provide is up-to-date and the opportunities we advertise are genuine, lawful and non-discriminatory. However, students are encouraged to do their own due diligence before making any decisions or applying for or accepting any opportunities.</span> </p>
<p><span class="lead"><strong>Paid Work with Careers and Employability</strong></span></p>
<p>We are delighted to be able to offer some paid posts for students to assist us with our careers activities. This includes the appointment of a Marketing and Administration Intern to assist us with our <a data-id="1656" href="/{localLink:umb://document/a191300696004f55b0bb224278abf75a}" title="Employer Mentoring">Employer Mentoring Programme.</a> </p>]]></Value>
